{"TopicId":154691,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"New flag for Mars?","CreatedByName":"NSEP","CreatedById":165635,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-08T15:40:36Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"NSEP","CreatedById":165635,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-08T15:40:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor anyone who didn\u0027t know yet, Mars has a flag, i dont know if it is official, but it looks like this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00222560px-Flag_of_Mars.svg.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022600\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ed/Flag_of_Mars.svg/2560px-Flag_of_Mars.svg.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe red\u00A0field means Mars now, and the green and blue mean the eventual terraformed Mars. The problem is: We dont know if we are actually going to terraform Mars. It\u0027s like adding a World map to a flag, representing world conquest, while the nation has never conquered the world. This map is maybe suitable for when we actually terraformed Mars, but not now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat do you think?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh and another thing to note: This is not really a thread about making a change, it is just a thought experiment thread thing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tex_NL","CreatedById":58254,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-08T15:50:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI did a Google search on the image and it indeed identified it as something to do with Mars. But it\u0027s nothing new. I found references as old as may 2011 (2004 after some digging). And all but one of the articles found were in Russian.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NSEP","CreatedById":165635,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-08T16:14:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222914554\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154691\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221483890642\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002258254\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Tex_NL\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n24 minutes ago, Tex_NL said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI did a Google search on the image and it indeed identified it as something to do with Mars. But it\u0027s nothing new. I found references as old as may 2011 (2004 after some digging). And all but one of the articles found were in Russian.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI read on Wikipedia that it originates from\u00A01998 and it was designed by NASA scientist Pascal Lee.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-01-08T16:15:26Z\u0022 title=\u002201/08/2017 04:15  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 8, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by NSEP\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scotius","CreatedById":57622,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-08T16:29:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s ugly. It looks like a cheap kitchen towel. And there is nothing even remotely suggesting \u0022Mars\u0022 when you look at it - because that red stripe isn\u0027t cutting it at all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-01-08T17:50:51Z\u0022 title=\u002201/08/2017 05:50  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 8, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Frybert\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EPlease don\u0026#039;t reaction image.\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NSEP","CreatedById":165635,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-08T16:34:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222914600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154691\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221483892979\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257622\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Scotius\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Scotius said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s ugly. It looks like a cheap kitchen towel. And there is nothing even remotely suggesting \u0022Mars\u0022 when you look at it - because that red stripe isn\u0027t cutting it at all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI agree, but the flag is still easy to reconize, wich is really important with flags.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-01-08T17:51:09Z\u0022 title=\u002201/08/2017 05:51  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 8, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Frybert\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scotius","CreatedById":57622,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-08T16:39:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes. but recognizable like this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022un-flag-flying-pole-blue-sky-behind-it.j\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.un.org/sites/www.un.org/files/styles/large/public/2014/11/24/un-flag-flying-pole-blue-sky-behind-it.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022eu-flags.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://static.snopes.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/eu-flags.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThree stripes of clashing colours? There are dozens of countries on Earth using similiar scheme - this one will simply disappear into the crowd, never to be seen again \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NSEP","CreatedById":165635,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-08T16:48:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222914613\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154691\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221483893571\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257622\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Scotius\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, Scotius said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes. but recognizable like this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022un-flag-flying-pole-blue-sky-behind-it.j\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.un.org/sites/www.un.org/files/styles/large/public/2014/11/24/un-flag-flying-pole-blue-sky-behind-it.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://static.snopes.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/eu-flags.jpg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022eu-flags.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 src=\u0022http://static.snopes.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/eu-flags.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThree stripes of clashing colours? There are dozens of countries on Earth using similiar scheme - this one will simply disappear into the crowd, never to be seen again \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, three stripes is easier to recoginze from far away than\u00A0the European flag from far away. Thats \u003Cspan\u003Ea main rule in flag designing. From far away, some flags look strikingly simulair or just a flag with 1 color. Symbols also need to be simple, for again, be regonizable from for away and not be a smudge.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-01-08T16:49:37Z\u0022 title=\u002201/08/2017 04:49  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 8, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by NSEP\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tex_NL","CreatedById":58254,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-08T17:48:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBoth ON and OFF topic:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/pnv5iKB2hl4?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-08T17:50:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks more like test picture to me, that flag. Double purpose I suppose ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Elthy","CreatedById":63317,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-08T18:13:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSince its not official its about as usefull as any paint image. Before we have a permanent settlement on mars everything regarding martionan flags is just nonsense...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnce we have a permanent mars settlement the people living there will make the decision, or someone at e.g. the UN.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Shpaget","CreatedById":45577,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-08T19:02:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222914586\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154691\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221483892084\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165635\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NSEP\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, NSEP said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI read on Wikipedia that it originates from\u00A01998 and it was designed by NASA scientist Pascal Lee.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGuess he\u0027s a huge fan of\u00A0Kim Stanley Robinson.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-08T20:19:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222914600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154691\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221483892979\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257622\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Scotius\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Scotius said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt looks like a cheap kitchen towel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis! Towel. A symbol of the humankind expansion through the space.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA towel is just about the most massively useful thing any interstellar Hitchhiker can carry.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA simple flag doesn\u0027t express enough the technical progress of the humanity.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would be at least animated (by its definition: say,\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u0022The national flag of the Martian Unity is an animated rectangle, containinng three coloured vertical bars (rgb, rgb, rgb), swapping around, with frame rate 5 fps.\u003Cbr\u003E\nIt\u0027s colors represent the future history of Mars, the greatest wishes of its future people: fresh tomatoes, green* (not orange) landscape, a pool full of blue water to take a bath\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*green\u00A0 - obsolete (on Mars) color, similar to the color of a indicator lamp under normal conditions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222914694\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154691\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221483897805\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002298447\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022YNM\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, YNM said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks more like test picture to me, that flag. Double purpose I suppose ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd a trolling of earthlings. Every TV on the Earth shows the Martian State Flag.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GDJ","CreatedById":58462,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-08T20:29:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI like this one.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022p03c1n4x.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://ichef.bbci.co.uk/wwfeatures/wm/live/624_351/images/live/p0/3c/1n/p03c1n4x.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-08T20:35:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReminds me of \u003Cem\u003EForrest Gump\u003C/em\u003E movie.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022p03c1n4x.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://ichef.bbci.co.uk/wwfeatures/wm/live/624_351/images/live/p0/3c/1n/p03c1n4x.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JetJaguar","CreatedById":146965,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-09T01:31:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222914829\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154691\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221483906741\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis! Towel. A symbol of the humankind expansion through the space.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, if you\u0027re going to be exploring\u00A0space, you should always know where your towel is.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ozymandias_the_Goat","CreatedById":159377,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-09T01:54:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Image result for watney ayyy\u0022 src=\u0022https://s-media-cache-ak0.pinimg.com/originals/39/f9/e3/39f9e308ea27135ca3d737837eb7cde0.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPut this on your flag!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"John22","CreatedById":172771,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-09T06:15:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222914546\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154691\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221483890037\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165635\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NSEP\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, NSEP said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ed/Flag_of_Mars.svg/2560px-Flag_of_Mars.svg.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00222560px-Flag_of_Mars.svg.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022600\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ed/Flag_of_Mars.svg/2560px-Flag_of_Mars.svg.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe design of the flag was originally conceived by\u00A0NASA\u00A0planetary scientist\u00A0Pascal Lee\u00A0during 1998.\u00A0In addition to symbolizing liberty as a tricolor flag, the design evokes a vision of the \u0022future history\u0022 of Mars in which the planet is transformed from red, to green, and then blue like the Earth.\u00A0 \u003Cspan style=\u0022text-indent:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;\u0022\u003E\u003Cfont color=\u0022#252525\u0022 face=\u0022sans-serif\u0022\u003EThere is no official flag for Mars because there\u00A0is no\u00A0government\u00A0\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(37,37,37);font-family:sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;\u0022\u003Eor other authority in existence capable of adopting such a flag.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wjolcz","CreatedById":39636,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-09T09:34:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot like Earth has a flag either.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would be nice to see the UN flag being planted in Martian soil..\u00A0That\u0027s never going to happen though lol.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Streetwind","CreatedById":98962,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-09T09:54:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, for Earth to have an official flag, you\u0027d first have to establish an authority that has the right to make it official - a right it would have to obtain through being recognized and accepted by every country on Earth. No such organization exists today; even the United Nations aren\u0027t that universally recognized.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn the upside, though, that\u0027s one problem that Mars won\u0027t have, or any other world or other orbital structure we colonize. We\u0027re starting them off fresh, so there\u0027s a reasonable likelyhood that it will be done in an at least somewhat structured manner. People are already pondering today how such a new colony might be governed, for example. Right now that is still idle speculation, but you can bet that that kind of thing will ramp up massively in both relevancy and quality once the first semi-permanent crew is training for their mission.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo in my opinion, we\u0027ll get an officially recognized Mars flag before we ever get an officially recognized Earth flag \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u00A0 If anything, Earth needs an official Mars flag as a boot to the butt to get its business in order! I have to agree with the overall sentiment in this thread though: that three-color piece of questionable artistic merit in the opening post is not something I\u0027d vote for in any flag. Mars or otherwise.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-01-09T09:56:30Z\u0022 title=\u002201/09/2017 09:56  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 9, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Streetwind\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"wumpus","CreatedById":133850,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-09T19:54:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWiki has a picture of the flag used in \u0022Stranger in a Strange Land\u0022 (a flag hastily made to fit legal and political realities of the book, not to be taken seriously even *inside* the book in question).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022330px-Flag_of_Mars_Stranger_in_a_Strange\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/Flag_of_Mars_Stranger_in_a_Strange_Land.svg/330px-Flag_of_Mars_Stranger_in_a_Strange_Land.svg.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Findthepin1","CreatedById":139989,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-09T22:30:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt shouldn\u0027t be up to anybody on Earth to decide what Mars\u0027 flag is. That\u0027s for colonists to decide.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-01-09T22:31:29Z\u0022 title=\u002201/09/2017 10:31  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 9, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Findthepin1\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mitchz95","CreatedById":82292,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-10T05:04:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222915989\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154691\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221483991684\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022133850\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022wumpus\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, wumpus said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWiki has a picture of the flag used in \u0022Stranger in a Strange Land\u0022 (a flag hastily made to fit legal and political realities of the book, not to be taken seriously even *inside* the book in question).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022330px-Flag_of_Mars_Stranger_in_a_Strange\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/Flag_of_Mars_Stranger_in_a_Strange_Land.svg/330px-Flag_of_Mars_Stranger_in_a_Strange_Land.svg.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou know, that\u0027s not bad. I could get behind that one. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-10T05:25:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222916184\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154691\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221484001049\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139989\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Findthepin1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, Findthepin1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt shouldn\u0027t be up to anybody on Earth to decide what Mars\u0027 flag is. That\u0027s for colonists to decide.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhatever they decide, it will be pale orange. Orange as omnipresent\u00A0dust and pale because\u00A0sun-bleached.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMartian Republic state anthem: \u003Cem\u003E50 Shades of Pale Orange\u003C/em\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222915989\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154691\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221483991684\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022133850\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022wumpus\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, wumpus said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022330px-Flag_of_Mars_Stranger_in_a_Strange\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/Flag_of_Mars_Stranger_in_a_Strange_Land.svg/330px-Flag_of_Mars_Stranger_in_a_Strange_Land.svg.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022Steal a rocket and scram to Earth\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}